properties.comments: False news of King Edward IV's death reached York on 6th.  Requiem Mass was sung on 7th
Indication that Richard was either in York and about to leave, or due to pass through on his way south or had already left
Richard met Edward V at Stony Stratford
City dignitaries welcomed Richard and Edward V

properties.location: Palace of the Bishop of London
properties.comments: Edward V at Palace of the Bishop of London
Edward V at the Tower of London
Reign of Richard III began.  King went to Westminster Hall and took his seat in the King's Bench, then went to St. Paul's
City of London, Baynard's Castle.  Great Seal handed to Bishop of Lincoln by King at 3pm in room in the chapel at Baynard's Castle
City of London. King probably still in Baynard's Castle
Oxford (Magdalen College) King heard disputations on moral philosophy
King toured the University (King probably left to spend night at Woodstock)
In a letter of summons addressed to various gentry, dated 18th August, the king said he expected to arrive at Pontefract on 27th August - he may have arrived earlier
King was to be met at Tadcaster by Sheriffs and at Breckles Mills by Mayor.  Kings arrival at Minster
Great Seal delivered to the King at noon in "King's Chamber" at Angel Inn
Priory of St John the Baptist East Stree
King entered London this day.  Met at Kennington by Mayor, etc
Great Seal returned to Chancellor in Star Chamber at Westminster by king
Twelfth Night feast in the White Hall at Westminster Mayor of London attended

properties.location: Priory of St. John of Jerusalem, Clerkenwell

properties.comments: King received Great Seal at seven in the evening in the chapel at Nottingham Castle
Lodge in the park of Beskwood
King probably moved to Leicester (see Introduction p xiv)
